# Novotroitskoye, Mishkinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Novotroitskoye () is a rural locality (a village) and the administrative centre of Novotroitsky Selsoviet, Mishkinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 450 as of 2010. There are 8 streets.
Geography
Novotroitskoye is located 33&nbsp;km northeast of Mishkino (the district's administrative centre) by road. Refandy is the nearest rural locality.
